01:30:42.350 --> 01:30:44.100
to a school in which
the people working it

01:30:44.100 --> 01:30:46.200
would never send their
children to Start there.

01:30:46.200 --> 01:30:48.325
The second thing is recognize
that the conversation

01:30:48.325 --> 01:30:50.324
around education in the
United States of America

01:30:50.324 --> 01:30:52.070
is driven by employment,
not education.

01:30:52.070 --> 01:30:54.300
That's why these are essentially
are boards of employment,

01:30:54.300 --> 01:30:55.300
not boards of education.

01:30:55.300 --> 01:30:58.010
The system is designed to
ensure that individuals

01:30:58.010 --> 01:30:59.720
who work in it stay employed.

01:30:59.720 --> 01:31:02.810
There's a shift in the
paradigm of professionalism.

01:31:02.810 --> 01:31:05.330
Unlike generations
from the past, where

01:31:05.330 --> 01:31:09.410
this generation of
professionals do not necessarily

01:31:09.410 --> 01:31:11.410
value job security.

01:31:11.410 --> 01:31:12.820
You value the product.

01:31:12.820 --> 01:31:15.330
And that doesn't happen in the
traditional public education

01:31:15.330 --> 01:31:16.870
system at the level it should.

01:31:16.870 --> 01:31:20.780
In fact, it's longevity that
gets you the greatest reward,

01:31:20.780 --> 01:31:22.057
as opposed to productivity.

01:31:22.057 --> 01:31:23.640
And so you have to
take the same model

01:31:23.640 --> 01:31:26.870
that you use here, that is
in, fact working, not just

01:31:26.870 --> 01:31:31.430
here but Uber and Airbnb,
where you're seeing

01:31:31.430 --> 01:31:33.280
a product that's meaningful.

01:31:33.280 --> 01:31:35.090
So you, as consumers,
whether or not you

01:31:35.090 --> 01:31:37.359
have children in the system,
you are in fact consumers

01:31:37.359 --> 01:31:39.650
because at the end of the
day, to Brother Jeff's point,

01:31:39.650 --> 01:31:41.630
you're going to
either employ or not

01:31:41.630 --> 01:31:43.760
employ Chicago Public
Schools; graduates.

01:31:43.760 --> 01:31:46.580
So there needs to be a
push from organizations

01:31:46.580 --> 01:31:48.290
such as this to push
for the very things

01:31:48.290 --> 01:31:49.790
that you want for
your own children,

01:31:49.790 --> 01:31:51.627
were you to have them,
if you have them,

01:31:51.627 --> 01:31:53.710
and that is to have access
to a quality education.

01:31:53.710 --> 01:31:56.850
I ask you to ask for nothing
more and nothing less.

01:31:56.850 --> 01:31:59.210
To what Brother
Stovall was saying,

01:31:59.210 --> 01:32:01.420
sometimes the conversation
is about equity.

01:32:01.420 --> 01:32:03.800
And freedom means that some
people need a little bit more

01:32:03.800 --> 01:32:05.591
in order to get equal,
because for so long,

01:32:05.591 --> 01:32:06.680
they have not gotten that.

01:32:06.680 --> 01:32:11.240
So for me, the bottom line
is if this school is so good,

01:32:11.240 --> 01:32:14.570
then no child should ever have
to be forced to attend it.

01:32:14.570 --> 01:32:16.830
They will attend it
because they wish to.

01:32:16.830 --> 01:32:20.650
School choice provides families
with the same opportunity that

01:32:20.650 --> 01:32:23.480
has been provided to the wealthy
and white Americans forever,

01:32:23.480 --> 01:32:25.611
because for the first
time in American history,

01:32:25.611 --> 01:32:27.860
we're actually having a
conversation about poor people

01:32:27.860 --> 01:32:29.910
who are saying, where are you
sending your child to school

01:32:29.910 --> 01:32:30.480
this year?

01:32:30.480 --> 01:32:34.890
That was a conversation that for
generations was confined only

01:32:34.890 --> 01:32:36.210
to the well-to-do.

01:32:36.210 --> 01:32:41.000
So I'm saying, with all due
haste, push as hard as you can

01:32:41.000 --> 01:32:44.020
for school choice, school
choice, school choice,

01:32:44.020 --> 01:32:47.770
because that is the only
strategy that will provide

01:32:47.770 --> 01:32:49.450
for access to a
quality education

01:32:49.450 --> 01:32:52.680
within the lifetime
of the children who

01:32:52.680 --> 01:32:54.550
are, in fact, in school.

01:32:54.550 --> 01:32:57.100
ROLAND MARTIN: I will
